Building, installing and using a simple package consisting in a main library ("dummy") and an auxiliary library ("utils")
The auxiliary library is used by the main library but can also be used by other packages.

To build the package
- cd ./build
- make 
- make test
- make install
- make opam.install 
- make opam.show (checks that a package with name "dummy" is not already installed) 

To use the package
- cd ../use
- make doc.view
- make 

To uninstall the package
- cd ../build
- make opam.remove



